Methods
-------
	Method is a group of statements which will perform certain tasks.
	we have to call the method through Object.
	
1. No Parameter		-	No Return Value
2. No Parameter		-	Return Value
3. Takes Parameter	-	No Return Value
4. Takes Parameter	-	Return Value

Ex: 1
	
	String s	= new String("Welcome");
	int len 	= s.length();		//No Parameter		-	Return Value
	String sub	= s.substrin(2,5)	//Takes Parameter	-	Return Value
	
	

Variables
---------
How many ways we can store data into variables
1) By using object reference variable
2) Method
3) Constructor



Methods:-
---------
1) Method name can be anything
2) Method may or may not return a value
3) If method is not returning any value then specify void
4) Method can take parameters/arguments
5) We have to invoke/call methods explicitly through object
6) Used for specifying logic
7) Method we have to invoke through object. (object.methodname)


Constructor:-
-------------
1) Constructor name should be same as class name
2) Constructor will never return a value(not even void)
3) We do not specify the void
4) Constructor can tale parameter/arguments
5) Constructor automatically invoked at the time of object creation
6) Used for initializing values of the variables
7) Constructor is a part of a class, it is also a method.
8) Constructor is only for initializing the values /storing data into the variable. We cannot perform any conditional statement or looping statement.

NOTE:-
------
Method is used for Assignment + Operations
Constructor is used for only Assignment


Constructor:- 2 - Type
-----------------------
1) Default Constructor
2) Parameterized Constructor